  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 16 April 2016 a 7.8-magnitude earthquake (Richter) struck off the coast of northern Ecuador. The epicenter was closest to the area between Cojim&#xED;es and Pedernales (Manab&#xED; province) nearby the Muisne canton (Esmeraldas province) and 170 kilometres northwest of the country s capital of Quito. Considerable damage was reported in the areas closest to the epicenter in the provinces of Manab&#xED; Esmeraldas Guayas and Pinchincha. The government initially declared a state of emergency in six provinces which was extended until mid-December in the provinces of Esmeraldas and Manab&#xED; 16 April 16- earthquake 18 April 16- DREF operation CHF 405 778 21 April 16- IFRC appeak CHF 18 350 386 to support 100k people over 12 months. 11 November 16- IFRC revised emergency appeal for CHF15m to assist 85 234</narrative>
  </description>
